is like a "program". The Hot Swap feature only modifies the instructions in the Memory at Runtime (i.e; to the Process in execution) by leveraging the Modified Harvard Architecture explained by AOS sir in today's lecture. 👍👍The actual program (APK) might get updated when this process finishes it's execution and is swapped out of memory depending upon the implementation of Android. 👍👍👍 :  Sahil Rasaikar: Idhar ka natki nahi chahiye :  Shashank Pal: Ktna padhega laxman! :  Sahil Rasaikar: ek no.👍 :  Sahil Rasaikar: Bhai jo padhne aaya tha wohi diye nahi :  Sahil Rasaikar: Elective me :  Sahil Rasaikar: Bin faltu ka RTOS padh rha :  Shashank Pal: Me to placement ke liye aya hu 😅 :  Ayush Bhanu: + :  Sahil Rasaikar: Bhai 😂 :  Sahil Rasaikar: Tu alag level pe chal rha hai :  Tirth Gandhi: <Media omitted> :  Prakhar: + :  Tirth Gandhi: Tumhara ho to gya bhai ab kya chahiye 😂 :  Prakhar: Bhai lakshya yahi hai kehna chaah ra😂 :  Shashank Pal: Tu ab padhai kr :  Sahil Rasaikar: Public :  Sahil Rasaikar: <Media omitted> :  Kumar Harshwardhan: Abhi form nahi bhare hai yaar :  Vineet Jain: Bhai kya ha yeah :  Kumar Harshwardhan: Anti ragging form :  Sahil Rasaikar: Anti ragging :  Vineet Jain: This message was deleted :  Vineet Jain: Okay :  Prikshit Sharma: Aree haan ye bi bharna hai ek to inke form khatam ni hote kabhi kch kabhi kch :  Prikshit Sharma: 😂 :  Prakhar: Ha bhai😂 :  Akshat Saxena: Parent ka hi dal de aur ky :  Kshitija Shirsekar: 😂😂😂 :  Ayush Bhanu: Ragging lene dene ka time bhi h kisis pe🤦🏻‍♂️ :  Sahil Rasaikar: 💯 :  Sahil Rasaikar: Maine ha mobile hi daal diya :  Sahil Rasaikar: 😂 :  Shishir Gupta: Kisi ko ccmt ka return payment mila kya??? This act is also referred to as an overlay. It is especially important in Unixlike systems, although it exists elsewhere. As no new process is created, the process identifier (PID) does not change, but the machine code, data, heap, and stack of the process are replaced by those of the new program. :  Vineet Jain: It will replace :  Sahil Rasaikar: Suno :  Rahi Bhensdadia: Entry size B haiTo ek page me kitni entries accomodate ho sakti hai wo count kiya. In drop trail gateways an arrival of a burst could result, in several losses. as most of the burst will be lost. IN Constrast in Red gateways, it drops packet early so as not to allow the quell to grow fully.So, when a burst arrives it will only drop some of the packers of the burst. The No. Of packets dropped will be roughly proportional to their share of bandwidth. hence bursty flow should losse fewer packet in RED.. :  Vineet Jain: This answer I will right :  Vineet Jain: In paper :  Tirth Gandhi: Bhai same maine likha tha 😂 :  Tirth Gandhi: 🥲 :  Vineet Jain: Bhai sir ko mail kar dey fir :  Kumar Harshwardhan: Mail mat kar.
